nnect 现已在纽约市、洛杉矶、迈阿密、拉斯维加斯、达拉斯、华盛顿特区等地推出。检查应用程序以查看您居住的地方是否可以使用该功能。</p><p>这是乘车共享平台采用的最新工具，旨在提高安全性并减少<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/lyfts-first-safety-report-4000-sexual-assault-cases-113547009.html">性侵犯和其他暴力事件。</a> Uber 最近让<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/uber-live-safety-agent-text-to-911-safety-toolkit-130047909.html">乘客和司机可以更轻松地联系 911</a>和现场安全人员。该平台还开始<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/uber-safety-features-audio-recordings-ridecheck-seat-belt-152849633.html">允许乘客和司机</a>在旅途中录制音频。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/lyft-expands-program-that-matches-women-and-nonbinary-riders-to-drivers-113016366.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/lyft-expands-program-that-matches-women-and-nonbinary-riders-to-drivers-113016366.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 568a145e-b44f-43bc-b315-81132c8aab87</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Lawrence Bonk]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Tue, 13 Feb 2024 11:30:16 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1707830977</ingested><modified> 2024-02-13T13:29:46+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="874" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-02%2F98243450-c527-11ee-8f7f-364ca8b70f89&amp;resize=1400%2C874&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=552d7fa8db1f11a2138d6cd84dcfe6e0711ad065" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="874" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-02%2F98243450-c527-11ee-8f7f-364ca8b70f89&amp;resize=1400%2C874&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=8e0d2c23456953d1d757691fc5d80e25621f6242" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Lyft]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Two images of the app showing the feature being used.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Lyft Women Connect+]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Amazon Prime Video won't offer Dolby Vision and Atmos on its ad-supported plan]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> 1 月 29 日，亚马逊<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazons-prime-video-will-start-serving-ads-on-january-29-unless-you-pay-extra-040529534.html">开始在 Prime Video 订阅者的观看体验中插入广告</a>。该公司去年<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazons-prime-video-will-show-ads-unless-you-pay-3-more-per-month-111709384.html">宣布了</a>这一变化，告诉客户它将开始在其服务的电影和节目中展示“有限的广告”，以便可以投资“引人注目的内容，并在很长一段时间内不断增加投资”。那些不想看广告的人必须每月支付3美元的额外费用。然而，它没有说的是，如果订阅者选择留在广告支持层，它也会取消他们对杜比功能的访问权限。德国科技出版物<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.4kfilme.de/amazon-prime-video-entfernt-dolby-atmos-und-dolby-vision-im-werbefinanzierten-abo/"><em>4kfilme</em></a>最先发现了这一变化，并得到了<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/johnarcher/2024/02/11/amazon-prime-videos-new-ads-based-subscription-has-a-surprise/?sh=6d742aa77cd5"><em>福布斯</em></a>的证实。</p><p> <em>《福布斯》</em>通过在支持该技术的电视上播放<em>《杰克·瑞恩》</em>的一集进行了测试，该剧集在支持该技术的电视上使用杜比视界高动态范围视频和杜比全景声声音进行编码。该出版物发现，当他们使用广告支持的帐户时，覆盖在视频顶部的确认杜比视界和全景声已启用的框丢失了。当使用无广告帐户玩游戏时，这些框会像往常一样显示。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>这意味着，如果客户想要继续播放启用杜比视界和全景声的视频，并且不希望自己的节目和电影被广告打断，那么他们必须在订阅费之外每月额外支付 3 美元。需要注意的是， <em>《福布斯》</em>还发现，无广告的帐户仍然可以访问 HDR10+，这是一项与杜比视界 (Dolby Vision) 相媲美的技术。</p><p>正如预期的那样，订阅者对这一变化感到不满，足以导致加州联邦法院<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/business/business-news/amazon-prime-video-ad-tier-lawsuit-1235822779/">对该公司提起</a>集体诉讼。该投诉指控亚马逊违反了消费者保护法，并称其对条款的改变具有“欺骗性”和“不公平”。它认为，那些已经支付了一年期 Prime 订阅费用的人希望像亚马逊所承诺的那样享受不间断的观看体验。但由于他们也受到了最近这一事态发展的影响，亚马逊正在“剥夺他们应有的合理期望”。该集体诉讼寻求至少 500 万美元的赔偿，并要求法院颁发禁令“禁止 [亚马逊] 的欺骗行为”。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/amazon-prime-video-wont-offer-dolby-vision-and-atmos-on-its-ad-supported-plan-093327322.html?src =rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/amazon-prime-video-wont-offer-dolby-vision-and-atmos-on-its-ad-supported-plan-093327322.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 31e05c3d-0b94-4ad8-8e52-20f2af29063b</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mariella Moon]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Tue, 13 Feb 2024 09:33:27 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1707816783</ingested><modified> 2024-02-13T09:33:07+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="827" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-02%2F6c4ed150-ca3b-11ee-b7fd-0a63eeee74cd&amp;resize=1400%2C827&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=a6b22c73b9f24d3f565ebdcbe3a116bbc03ac106" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]